A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the House Study Committee on an At-Risk Populations Abuse Registry; and for
2 other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, individuals who have been substantiated to have committed abuse, neglect, or
4 exploitation of at-risk populations, including individuals with disabilities and older adults,
5 should be properly documented to prevent future harm; and
6 WHEREAS, other states, including Tennessee, have established registries to track
7 individuals who have engaged in such conduct; and
8 WHEREAS, a comprehensive study is necessary to determine the feasibility, structure, and
9 implementation of a similar registry in Georgia, including considerations of due process,
10 enforcement, and interagency coordination; and
11 WHEREAS, the purpose of this Resolution is to establish a study committee to examine and
12 make recommendations on the establishment of a substantiated abuse registry for at-risk
13 populations; and
